title: Summary of Demographics and Baseline Characteristics by Treatment Group
footnotes: Percentages based on non-missing values. P-values: chi-square for categorical, ANOVA for continuous. ITT population.

title: Subject Disposition
footnotes: ITT population. Percentages based on number of randomized subjects. Reasons for discontinuation coded per protocol.

title: Protocol Deviations by Category and Treatment Group
footnotes: Safety population. Major deviations defined per protocol Section 9.5.

title: Medical History by System Organ Class
footnotes: Safety population. Coded using MedDRA v27.0. Subjects counted once per SOC.

title: Summary of Adverse Events by System Organ Class and Preferred Term
footnotes: Safety population. Events coded using MedDRA v27.0. Subjects counted once per PT within each SOC.

title: Summary of Adverse Events by Maximum Severity
footnotes: Safety population. Severity graded per CTCAE v5.0. Subjects counted at maximum severity.

title: Summary of Treatment-Related Adverse Events
footnotes: Safety population. Causality assessed by investigator. Events with relationship Probable or Definite.

title: Summary of Serious Adverse Events
footnotes: Safety population. SAEs per ICH E2A definition. Includes onset date, duration, outcome, and action taken.

title: Summary of Adverse Events Leading to Discontinuation
footnotes: Safety population. Subjects who discontinued study drug due to an adverse event.

title: Summary of Hypoglycemic Events by Classification
footnotes: Safety population. Classification: documented symptomatic, asymptomatic, severe, probable symptomatic, relative. Per ADA criteria.

title: Summary of HbA1c by Visit and Treatment Group
footnotes: ITT population. LOCF applied for missing post-baseline values. Change from baseline calculated.

title: Summary of Fasting Plasma Glucose by Visit and Treatment Group
footnotes: ITT population. LOCF applied. Central lab values only.

title: Summary of Lipid Panel by Visit and Treatment Group
footnotes: ITT population. Total cholesterol, LDL-C, HDL-C, triglycerides. Fasting samples only.

title: Shift Table for Liver Function Tests
footnotes: Safety population. Shift from baseline to worst post-baseline value. CTCAE grade categories.

title: Summary of Vital Signs by Visit and Treatment Group
footnotes: Safety population. Systolic BP, diastolic BP, pulse, weight. Change from baseline.

title: Summary of Body Weight Change from Baseline
footnotes: ITT population. Observed values and LOCF. Categorical analysis: gained/lost/stable.

title: Summary of ECG Parameters by Visit
footnotes: Safety population. QTcF interval. Categorical analysis per ICH E14 thresholds.

title: Analysis of Primary Endpoint: Change from Baseline in HbA1c at Week 24
footnotes: ITT population. MMRM analysis. Model includes treatment, visit, baseline HbA1c, treatment-by-visit interaction.

title: Analysis of Key Secondary Endpoint: HbA1c Responder Rate at Week 24
footnotes: ITT population. Responder defined as HbA1c < 7.0%. Logistic regression adjusted for baseline HbA1c.

title: Subgroup Analysis of Primary Endpoint by Baseline Characteristics
footnotes: ITT population. Forest plot data. Subgroups: age (<65, >=65), sex, race, baseline HbA1c (<8.5, >=8.5).

title: Summary of Concomitant Medications by ATC Class
footnotes: Safety population. Coded using WHO Drug Dictionary March 2026. Medications taken during treatment period.

title: Kaplan-Meier Plot of Time to First Hypoglycemic Event
footnotes: ITT population. Subjects censored at last known follow-up. Log-rank test p-value shown.

title: Mean Change from Baseline in HbA1c Over Time by Treatment Group
footnotes: ITT population. LOCF. Error bars represent 95% CI. Dashed line at HbA1c = 7.0%.

title: Forest Plot of Primary Endpoint by Subgroup
footnotes: ITT population. Point estimates and 95% CI for LS mean difference vs placebo.

title: Waterfall Plot of Individual HbA1c Change from Baseline at Week 24
footnotes: ITT population. Each bar represents one subject. Colored by treatment group.

title: Mean Change from Baseline in Body Weight Over Time by Treatment Group
footnotes: ITT population. Observed values. Error bars represent standard error.

title: Scatter Plot of HbA1c Change vs Body Weight Change at Week 24
footnotes: ITT population. Each point represents one subject. Regression line with 95% CI.

title: Individual Subject Demographics Data
footnotes: All randomized subjects. Sorted by site and subject number.

title: Listing of Subjects Who Discontinued Early
footnotes: All randomized subjects who discontinued before Week 24. Includes reason and last visit date.

title: Listing of Serious Adverse Events
footnotes: Safety population. All SAEs. Includes verbatim term, coded term, onset, duration, outcome, causality.

title: Listing of Adverse Events Leading to Study Drug Discontinuation
footnotes: Safety population. Includes verbatim term, coded SOC/PT, onset date, severity, action taken.

title: Listing of Laboratory Values Outside Normal Range
footnotes: Safety population. Includes test name, visit, result, normal range, CTCAE grade.

title: Listing of Protocol Deviations
footnotes: All randomized subjects with major protocol deviations. Includes category, description, date.

title: Listing of Concomitant Medications
footnotes: Safety population. All medications taken during treatment period. Coded to ATC class and preferred name.
